Thank you

Version: 0.6.8, Python 3.5.2+ on Debian "testing" stream.

I've noticed that @roles_required will fail to check the role if it is placed outside of the @app.route decorator, as in:

    @roles_required('administrator')
    @app.route('/admin')
    def admin_panel():
        # endpoint logic here

This is as specified in the docs here: https://pythonhosted.org/Flask-User/authorization.html#roles-required

This was tested by attempting to access the page as both a non-"administrator" non-anonymous user and an "administrator" user. I could access admin-only pages with both accounts.

The following works as expected:

    @app.route('/admin')
    @roles_required('administrator')
    def admin_panel():
        # endpoint logic here

This works as expected (only the "administrator" user account can access this page; the other account results in an access error flash).

flask-login's @login_required works fine in either position.

